1. Ja ću *umreti* od smeha ako nastaviš tako da pričaš. (I will *die* laughing if you keep talking like that.)
2. Oni *umiru* od tuge jer su izgubili svog ljubimca. (They are *dying* of sadness because they lost their pet.)
3. Molim te da ne pričaš o tome jer ću *umreti* od sramote. (Please don't talk about it because I will *die* of embarrassment.)
4. Nažalost, moj deda je *umro* prošle godine. (Unfortunately, my grandfather *died* last year.)
5. Čovek je *umro* prirodnom smrću. (The man *died* of natural causes.)
6. Ubrzo nakon što su ga upucali, kriminalac je *umro* u bolnici. (Shortly after being shot, the criminal *died* in the hospital.)
7. Oni će *umreti* od gladi ako ne dobiju hranu. (They will *die* of hunger if they don't get food.)
8. Njeni roditelji će *umreti* od sreće kada čuju vesti. (Her parents will *die* of happiness when they hear the news.)
9. Mnogi ljudi su *umrli* u prošlosti zbog nedostatka lekova i medicinskih tretmana. (Many people *died* in the past due to a lack of medicine and medical treatments.)
10. Oni su bili toliko pijani da su jedva *umeli* da hodaju. (They were so drunk that they could barely *walk*.)